<Layout title="About" description="Who built Synaplex and why its work is exposed in public.">
  <p class="eyebrow">About</p><h1>Built to make epistemic state inspectable.</h1><p class="lede">Synaplex is designed and operated by <a href="https://github.com/evanfollis">Evan Follis</a>. It is an experiment in whether autonomous research can keep its sources, conjectures, Claims, Evidence, Decisions, failures, and engineering lessons legible to outsiders.</p>
  <div class="section prose"><h2>Why public?</h2><p>A polished conclusion is easy to overread. The public surface therefore exposes the empty findings set, blocked and disposed research, source provenance, preregistration boundary, and implementation receipts alongside any future accepted knowledge.</p><h2>Inspect the implementation</h2><p>The source, schemas, tests, and history are available in the <a href="https://github.com/evanfollis/synaplex">public repository ↗</a>. Machine readers can consume the <a href="/knowledge/public-projection.json">versioned projection</a>.</p></div>
</Layout>
